to the editor where is the touted diversity in the nominations for the bush administration front page jan 3 there is not a single jew in the lineup there is only one democrat there is no person with any ties to the labor union movement 's 16 million members although a majority of the nation supports a woman 's right to choose the only pro choice appointees have been placed in positions where these views are irrelevant a third of republican voters describe themselves as moderates and liberals but they are barely represented the incoming executive branch constitutes a conservative takeover of government without the legitimacy of a popular mandate gerald m pomper new brunswick nj jan 3 2001 the writer is a professor of political science at rutgers university

